statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.name: turnovers
statistics.description: The number of times a player loses possession to the other team.

statistics.name: minutes
statistics.description: The total number of minutes played.

statistics.name: assistTurnoverRatio
statistics.description: The average number of assists a player or team records per turnover

statistics.name: rebounds
statistics.description: The total number of rebounds (offensive and defensive).

statistics.name: defensiveRebounds
statistics.description: The number of times when the defense obtains the possession of the ball after a missed shot by the offense.

article.headline: Tennessee Tech 113, Hiwassee 42
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. -- Jud Dillard scored 19 points to lead six players in double figures as Tennessee Tech routed Hiwassee College 113-42 on Thursday night. The Golden Eagles (3-5) were 44 of 74 from the field (59.5 percent) and led 47-19 at halftime. Liam McMorrow and Kevin Murphy scored 15 points each. Chase Dunn scored 14 and Dennis Ogbe and Alfred Jones had 11 points apiece. McMorrow also grabbed 12 rebounds for his first career double-double. Tennessee Tech forced a school record 37 turnovers and outrebounded the Tigers 51-25. The previous mark for forced turnovers in a game was 29, which was set on Dec. 15, 1980, against Clinch Valley. The Golden Eagles also forced 26 steals, tying a school record set on Nov. 22, 1991, against Covenant College. Zach Williams scored 15 points to lead the Tigers, a Division II member of the United States Collegiate Athletic Association (USCAA).
